CM_ "J1939 messages without part -7x";
CM_ BO_ 3221225472 "This is a message for not used signals, created by Vector CANdb++ DBC OLE DB Provider.";
CM_ SG_ 3221225472 NetworkMessageControlByte "Identifies the function or service of an instance of the Network Message.  
A summary of the Network Message Control Bytes value assignments are defined within SAE J1939-31.";
CM_ BO_ 2555313918 "FD Transport Protocol - Data Transfer Message. 
The FD.TP.DT (DT) message is used to transmit each segment of PG data within a FD Transport session.";
CM_ BO_ 2555248382 "FD Transport Protocol - Connection Management Message.
The FD.TP.CM message is used to initiate and close FD Transport connections and, for RTS/CTS transfers, control the data flow.";
CM_ BO_ 2552626942 "FEFF Form of Multi-PG. 
Is transmitted using the D_PDU1 format.
This allows them to be sent either to a specific destination or to the global destination.";
CM_ BO_ 2148466430 "Safety Header Message. 
The SHM is transmitted with each instance of a Safety Data Message as part of a Safety Data Group and provides CRC and sequencing data.";
CM_ SG_ 2148466430 InvertedPF "Inverted PDU Format of SDM";
CM_ SG_ 2148466430 InvertedPS "Inverted PDU Specific of SDM";
CM_ SG_ 2148466430 InvertedSA "Inverted Source Address of SDM";
CM_ SG_ 2148466430 InvertedEDP "Inverted Extended Data Page of SDM";
CM_ SG_ 2148466430 InvertedDP "Inverted Data Page of SDM";
CM_ SG_ 2148466430 CRCofSdmData "32-bit CRC of the data field of SDM";
CM_ SG_ 2148466430 SequenceNumberOfSDG "Sequence Number of Safety Data Group";
CM_ BO_ 2559835902 "NAME Management Message
A message to change fields of the NAME of a CA";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 ErrorCode "When  the  NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 “Set Pending NAME”, NAME checksum is used as a check to ensure the NM message has been sent to the correct CA.";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 CommandedAAC "When the NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 – Set Pending NAME and the Arbitrary Address Capable Qualifier Flag (SPN 5665) is set to “0”";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 CommandedIndustryGroup "When the NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 – Set Pending NAME and the Industry Group Qualifier Flag (SPN 5664) is set to “0”";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 CommandedVehicleSystemInstance "When the NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 – Set Pending NAME and the Vehicle System Instance Qualifier Flag (SPN 5663) is set to “0”";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 CommandedVehicleSystem "When the NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 – Set Pending NAME and the Vehicle System Qualifier Flag (SPN 5662) is set to “0”";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 CommandedFunction "When the NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 – Set Pending NAME and the Function Qualifier Flag (SPN 5661) is set to “0”";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 CommandedFunctionInstance "When the NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 – Set Pending NAME and the Function Instance Qualifier Flag (SPN 5660) is set to “0”";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 CommandedECUInstance "When the NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 – Set Pending NAME and the ECU Instance Qualifier Flag (SPN 5659) is set to “0”";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 CommandedManufacturerCode "When the NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 – Set Pending NAME and the Manufacturer Code Qualifier Flag (SPN 5658) is set to “0”";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 NMControlModeIndicator "This four bit parameter is used to define the purpose of the NM message.";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 AACQualifierFlag "When the NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 – Set Pending NAME, this qualifier flag is used to indicate whether the Arbitrary Address Capable field (SPN  5674) shall be used";
CM_ SG_ 2559835902 IndustryGroupQualifierFlag "When the NM Control Mode Indicator is set to Mode 0 – Set Pending NAME, this qualifier flag is used to indicate whether the Industry Group field (SPN 5673) shall be used";
